msdpMIB.description: An experimental MIB module for MSDP Management and Monitoring. Copyright (C) The Internet Society 2006. This version of this MIB module is part of RFC 4624; see the RFC itself for full legal notices.

msdpEnabled.name: msdpEnabled
msdpEnabled.description: The state of MSDP on this MSDP speaker - globally enabled or disabled. Changes to this object should be stored to non-volatile memory.

msdpCacheLifetime.name: msdpCacheLifetime
msdpCacheLifetime.description: The lifetime given to SA cache entries when created or refreshed. This is the [SG-State-Period] in the MSDP spec. A value of 0 means no SA caching is done by this MSDP speaker. Changes to this object should be stored to non-volatile memory. This object does not measure time per se; instead, it is the delta from the time at which an SA message is received at which it should be expired if not refreshed. (i.e., it is the value of msdpSACacheExpiryTime immediately after receiving an SA message applying to that row.) As such, TimeInterval would be a more appropriate SYNTAX; it remains TimeTicks for backwards compatibility.

msdpNumSACacheEntries.name: msdpNumSACacheEntries
msdpNumSACacheEntries.description: The total number of entries in the SA Cache table.

msdpRPAddress.name: msdpRPAddress
msdpRPAddress.description: The Rendezvous Point (RP) address used when sourcing MSDP SA messages. May be 0.0.0.0 on non-RPs. Changes to this object should be stored to non-volatile memory.

msdpRequestsTable.name: msdpRequestsTable
msdpRequestsTable.description: The (conceptual) table listing group ranges and MSDP peers used when deciding where to send an SA Request message, when required. If SA Requests are not enabled, this table may be empty. In order to choose a peer to whom to send an SA Request for a given group, G, the subset of entries in this table whose (msdpRequestsPeerType, msdpRequestsPeer) tuple represents a peer whose msdpPeerState is established are examined. The set is further reduced by examining only those entries for which msdpPeerRequestsGroupAddressType equals the address type of G. The entries with the highest value of msdpRequestsGroupPrefix are considered, where the group G falls within the range described by the combination of msdpRequestsGroup and msdpRequestsGroupPrefix. (This sequence is commonly known as a 'longest-match' lookup.) Finally, if multiple entries remain, the entry with the lowest value of msdpRequestsPriority is chosen. The SA Request message is sent to the peer described by this row.

msdpRequestsEntry.name: msdpRequestsEntry
msdpRequestsEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) representing a group range used when deciding where to send an SA Request message.

msdpRequestsGroupAddress.name: msdpRequestsGroupAddress
msdpRequestsGroupAddress.description: The group address that, when combined with the mask in this entry, represents the group range to which this row applies.

msdpRequestsGroupMask.name: msdpRequestsGroupMask
msdpRequestsGroupMask.description: The mask that, when combined with the group address in this entry, represents the group range to which this row applies.

msdpRequestsPeer.name: msdpRequestsPeer
msdpRequestsPeer.description: The peer to which MSDP SA Requests for groups matching this entry's group range will be sent. This object, combined with msdpRequestsPeerType, must match the INDEX of a row in the msdpPeerTable, and to be considered, this peer's msdpPeerState must be established.

msdpRequestsStatus.name: msdpRequestsStatus
msdpRequestsStatus.description: The status of this row, by which new rows may be added to the table or old rows may be deleted.

msdpPeerTable.name: msdpPeerTable
msdpPeerTable.description: The (conceptual) table listing the MSDP speaker's peers.

msdpPeerEntry.name: msdpPeerEntry
msdpPeerEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) representing an MSDP peer. If row creation is supported, dynamically added rows are added to the system's stable configuration (corresponding to a StorageType value of nonVolatile).

msdpPeerRemoteAddress.name: msdpPeerRemoteAddress
msdpPeerRemoteAddress.description: The address of the remote MSDP peer.

msdpPeerState.name: msdpPeerState
msdpPeerState.description: The state of the MSDP TCP connection with this peer.

msdpPeerRPFFailures.name: msdpPeerRPFFailures
msdpPeerRPFFailures.description: The number of SA messages received from this peer that failed the Peer-RPF check. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the management system, and at other times as indicated by the value of msdpPeerDiscontinuityTime.

msdpPeerInSAs.name: msdpPeerInSAs
msdpPeerInSAs.description: The number of MSDP SA messages received on this connection. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the management system, and at other times as indicated by the value of msdpPeerDiscontinuityTime.

msdpPeerOutSAs.name: msdpPeerOutSAs
msdpPeerOutSAs.description: The number of MSDP SA messages transmitted on this connection. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the management system, and at other times as indicated by the value of msdpPeerDiscontinuityTime.

msdpPeerInSARequests.name: msdpPeerInSARequests
msdpPeerInSARequests.description: The number of MSDP SA-Request messages received on this connection. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the management system, and at other times as indicated by the value of msdpPeerDiscontinuityTime.

msdpPeerOutSARequests.name: msdpPeerOutSARequests
msdpPeerOutSARequests.description: The number of MSDP SA-Request messages transmitted on this connection. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the management system, and at other times as indicated by the value of msdpPeerDiscontinuityTime.

msdpPeerInSAResponses.name: msdpPeerInSAResponses
msdpPeerInSAResponses.description: The number of MSDP SA-Response messages received on this connection. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the management system, and at other times as indicated by the value of msdpPeerDiscontinuityTime.

msdpPeerOutSAResponses.name: msdpPeerOutSAResponses
msdpPeerOutSAResponses.description: The number of MSDP SA Response messages transmitted on this TCP connection. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the management system, and at other times as indicated by the value of msdpPeerDiscontinuityTime.

msdpPeerInControlMessages.name: msdpPeerInControlMessages
msdpPeerInControlMessages.description: The total number of MSDP messages, excluding encapsulated data packets, received on this TCP connection. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the management system, and at other times as indicated by the value of msdpPeerDiscontinuityTime.

msdpPeerOutControlMessages.name: msdpPeerOutControlMessages
msdpPeerOutControlMessages.description: The total number of MSDP messages, excluding encapsulated data packets, transmitted on this TCP connection. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the management system, and at other times as indicated by the value of msdpPeerDiscontinuityTime.

msdpPeerInDataPackets.name: msdpPeerInDataPackets
msdpPeerInDataPackets.description: The total number of encapsulated data packets received from this peer. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the management system, and at other times as indicated by the value of msdpPeerDiscontinuityTime.

msdpPeerOutDataPackets.name: msdpPeerOutDataPackets
msdpPeerOutDataPackets.description: The total number of encapsulated data packets sent to this peer. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the management system, and at other times as indicated by the value of msdpPeerDiscontinuityTime.

msdpPeerFsmEstablishedTransitions.name: msdpPeerFsmEstablishedTransitions
msdpPeerFsmEstablishedTransitions.description: The total number of times the MSDP FSM transitioned into the ESTABLISHED state.

msdpPeerFsmEstablishedTime.name: msdpPeerFsmEstablishedTime
msdpPeerFsmEstablishedTime.description: This timestamp is set to the value of sysUpTime when a peer transitions into or out of the ESTABLISHED state. It is set to zero when the MSDP speaker is booted.

msdpPeerInMessageTime.name: msdpPeerInMessageTime
msdpPeerInMessageTime.description: The sysUpTime value when the last MSDP message was received from the peer. It is set to zero when the MSDP speaker is booted.

msdpPeerLocalAddress.name: msdpPeerLocalAddress
msdpPeerLocalAddress.description: The local IP address used for this entry's MSDP TCP connection.

msdpPeerConnectRetryInterval.name: msdpPeerConnectRetryInterval
msdpPeerConnectRetryInterval.description: Time interval, in seconds, for the [ConnectRetry-period] for this peer.

msdpPeerHoldTimeConfigured.name: msdpPeerHoldTimeConfigured
msdpPeerHoldTimeConfigured.description: Time interval, in seconds, for the [HoldTime-Period] configured for this MSDP speaker with this peer. If the value of this object is zero (0), the MSDP connection is never torn down due to the absence of messages from the peer.

msdpPeerKeepAliveConfigured.name: msdpPeerKeepAliveConfigured
msdpPeerKeepAliveConfigured.description: Time interval, in seconds, for the [KeepAlive-Period] configured for this MSDP speaker with this peer. If the value of this object is zero (0), no periodic KEEPALIVE messages are sent to the peer after the MSDP connection has been established.

msdpPeerDataTtl.name: msdpPeerDataTtl
msdpPeerDataTtl.description: The minimum TTL a packet is required to have before it may be forwarded using SA encapsulation to this peer.

msdpPeerProcessRequestsFrom.name: msdpPeerProcessRequestsFrom
msdpPeerProcessRequestsFrom.description: This object indicates whether to process MSDP SA Request messages from this peer. If True(1), MSDP SA Request messages from this peer are processed and replied to (if appropriate) with SA Response messages. If False(2), MSDP SA Request messages from this peer are silently ignored. It defaults to False when msdpCacheLifetime is 0 and to True when msdpCacheLifetime is non-0. This object is deprecated because MSDP SA Requests were removed from the MSDP specification.

msdpPeerStatus.name: msdpPeerStatus
msdpPeerStatus.description: The RowStatus object by which peers can be added and deleted. A transition to 'active' will cause the MSDP 'Enable MSDP peering with P' Event to be generated. A transition out of the 'active' state will cause the MSDP 'Disable MSDP peering with P' Event to be generated. Care should be used in providing write access to this object without adequate authentication. msdpPeerRemoteAddress is the only variable that must be set to a valid value before the row can be activated. Since this is the table's INDEX, a row can be activated by simply setting the msdpPeerStatus variable. It is possible to modify other columns in the same conceptual row when the status value is active(1).

msdpPeerRemotePort.name: msdpPeerRemotePort
msdpPeerRemotePort.description: The remote port for the TCP connection between the MSDP peers.

msdpPeerLocalPort.name: msdpPeerLocalPort
msdpPeerLocalPort.description: The local port for the TCP connection between the MSDP peers.

msdpPeerEncapsulationType.name: msdpPeerEncapsulationType
msdpPeerEncapsulationType.description: The encapsulation in use when encapsulating data in SA messages to this peer.

msdpPeerConnectionAttempts.name: msdpPeerConnectionAttempts
msdpPeerConnectionAttempts.description: The number of times the state machine has transitioned from INACTIVE to CONNECTING.

msdpPeerInNotifications.name: msdpPeerInNotifications
msdpPeerInNotifications.description: The number of MSDP Notification messages received from this peer. This object is deprecated because MSDP Notifications have been removed from the spec.

msdpPeerOutNotifications.name: msdpPeerOutNotifications
msdpPeerOutNotifications.description: The number of MSDP Notification messages transmitted to this peer. This object is deprecated because MSDP Notifications have been removed from the spec.

msdpPeerLastError.name: msdpPeerLastError
msdpPeerLastError.description: The last error code and subcode received via Notification from this peer. If no error has occurred, this field is zero. Otherwise, the first byte of this two-byte OCTET STRING contains the O-bit and error code, and the second byte contains the subcode. This object is deprecated because MSDP Notifications have been removed from the spec.

msdpPeerDiscontinuityTime.name: msdpPeerDiscontinuityTime
msdpPeerDiscontinuityTime.description: The value of sysUpTime on the most recent occasion at which one or more of this entry's counters suffered a discontinuity. See the DESCRIPTION of each object to see if it is expected to have discontinuities. These discontinuities may occur at peer connection establishment. If no such discontinuities have occurred since the last reinitialization of the local management subsystem, then this object contains a zero value.

msdpSACacheTable.name: msdpSACacheTable
msdpSACacheTable.description: The (conceptual) table listing the MSDP SA advertisements currently in the MSDP speaker's cache.

msdpSACacheEntry.name: msdpSACacheEntry
msdpSACacheEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) representing an MSDP SA advertisement. The INDEX to this table includes msdpSACacheOriginRP for diagnosing incorrect MSDP advertisements; normally, a Group and Source pair would be unique. Row creation is not permitted; msdpSACacheStatus may only be used to delete rows from this table.

msdpSACacheGroupAddr.name: msdpSACacheGroupAddr
msdpSACacheGroupAddr.description: The group address of the SA Cache entry.

msdpSACacheSourceAddr.name: msdpSACacheSourceAddr
msdpSACacheSourceAddr.description: The source address of the SA Cache entry.

msdpSACacheOriginRP.name: msdpSACacheOriginRP
msdpSACacheOriginRP.description: The RP of the SA Cache entry. This field is in the INDEX in order to catch multiple RP's advertising the same source and group.

msdpSACachePeerLearnedFrom.name: msdpSACachePeerLearnedFrom
msdpSACachePeerLearnedFrom.description: The peer from which this SA Cache entry was last accepted. This address must correspond to the msdpPeerRemoteAddress value for a row in the MSDP Peer Table. This should be 0.0.0.0 on the router that originated the entry.

msdpSACacheRPFPeer.name: msdpSACacheRPFPeer
msdpSACacheRPFPeer.description: The peer from which an SA message corresponding to this cache entry would be accepted (i.e., the RPF peer for msdpSACacheOriginRP). This may be different than msdpSACachePeerLearnedFrom if this entry was created by an MSDP SA-Response. This address must correspond to the msdpPeerRemoteAddress value for a row in the MSDP Peer Table, or it may be 0.0.0.0 if no RPF peer exists.

msdpSACacheInSAs.name: msdpSACacheInSAs
msdpSACacheInSAs.description: The number of MSDP SA messages received relevant to this cache entry. This object must be initialized to zero when creating a cache entry.

msdpSACacheInDataPackets.name: msdpSACacheInDataPackets
msdpSACacheInDataPackets.description: The number of MSDP-encapsulated data packets received relevant to this cache entry. This object must be initialized to zero when creating a cache entry.

msdpSACacheUpTime.name: msdpSACacheUpTime
msdpSACacheUpTime.description: The time since this entry was first placed in the SA cache. The first epoch is the time that the entry was first placed in the SA cache, and the second epoch is the current time.

msdpSACacheExpiryTime.name: msdpSACacheExpiryTime
msdpSACacheExpiryTime.description: The time remaining before this entry will expire from the SA cache. The first epoch is now, and the second epoch is the time that the entry will expire.

msdpSACacheStatus.name: msdpSACacheStatus
msdpSACacheStatus.description: The status of this row in the table. The only allowable actions are to retrieve the status, which will be 'active', or to set the status to 'destroy' in order to remove this entry from the cache. Row creation is not permitted. No columnar objects are writable, so there are none that may be changed while the status value is active(1).

msdpMeshGroupTable.name: msdpMeshGroupTable
msdpMeshGroupTable.description: The (conceptual) table listing MSDP Mesh Group configuration.

msdpMeshGroupEntry.name: msdpMeshGroupEntry
msdpMeshGroupEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) representing a peer in an MSDP Mesh Group. If row creation is supported, dynamically added rows are added to the system's stable configuration (corresponding to a StorageType value of nonVolatile).

msdpMeshGroupName.name: msdpMeshGroupName
msdpMeshGroupName.description: The name of the mesh group.

msdpMeshGroupPeerAddress.name: msdpMeshGroupPeerAddress
msdpMeshGroupPeerAddress.description: A peer address that is a member of the mesh group with name msdpMeshGroupName. The msdpMeshGroupPeerAddress must match a row in the msdpPeerTable.

msdpMeshGroupStatus.name: msdpMeshGroupStatus
msdpMeshGroupStatus.description: This entry's status, by which new entries may be added to the table and old entries deleted. msdpMeshGroupName and msdpMeshGroupPeerAddress must be set to valid values before the row can be activated. Since these are the table's INDEX, a row can be activated by simply setting the msdpMeshGroupStatus variable. It is not possible to modify other columns in the same conceptual row when the status value is active(1), because the only other objects in the row are part of the INDEX. Changing one of these changes the row, so an old row must be deleted and a new one created.

msdpEstablished.name: msdpEstablished
msdpEstablished.description: The MSDP Established event is generated when the MSDP FSM enters the ESTABLISHED state.

msdpBackwardTransition.name: msdpBackwardTransition
msdpBackwardTransition.description: The MSDPBackwardTransition Event is generated when the MSDP FSM moves from a higher-numbered state to a lower-numbered state.

msdpMIBCompliance.name: msdpMIBCompliance
msdpMIBCompliance.description: The compliance statement for entities that implement a pre- RFC version of MSDP. This statement is deprecated because it includes objects used for managing/monitoring aspects of MSDP that were removed before it was published as an RFC.

msdpMIBFullCompliance.name: msdpMIBFullCompliance
msdpMIBFullCompliance.description: The compliance statement for entities that implement MSDP (RFC3618).

msdpMIBReadOnlyCompliance.name: msdpMIBReadOnlyCompliance
msdpMIBReadOnlyCompliance.description: The compliance statement for entities that implement MSDP (RFC3618), but do not permit configuration (or only permit partial configuration) via SNMP.

msdpMIBGlobalsGroup.name: msdpMIBGlobalsGroup
msdpMIBGlobalsGroup.description: A collection of objects providing information on global MSDP state.

msdpMIBPeerGroup.name: msdpMIBPeerGroup
msdpMIBPeerGroup.description: A collection of objects for managing MSDP peers. This group is deprecated in favor of msdpMIBPeerGroup2 because it contains objects for managing aspects of MSDP that were removed before it was published as an RFC.

msdpMIBEncapsulationGroup.name: msdpMIBEncapsulationGroup
msdpMIBEncapsulationGroup.description: A collection of objects for managing encapsulations if the MSDP encapsulation interfaces are not given interface indices.

msdpMIBSACacheGroup.name: msdpMIBSACacheGroup
msdpMIBSACacheGroup.description: A collection of objects for managing MSDP SA cache entries.

msdpMIBNotificationGroup.name: msdpMIBNotificationGroup
msdpMIBNotificationGroup.description: A collection of notifications for signaling changes in MSDP peer relationships.

msdpMIBRequestsGroup.name: msdpMIBRequestsGroup
msdpMIBRequestsGroup.description: A collection of objects for managing MSDP Request transmission. This group is deprecated because Requests were removed from MSDP before its publication as an RFC.

msdpMIBRPGroup.name: msdpMIBRPGroup
msdpMIBRPGroup.description: A collection of objects for MSDP speakers that source MSDP messages.

msdpMIBMeshGroupGroup.name: msdpMIBMeshGroupGroup
msdpMIBMeshGroupGroup.description: A collection of objects for MSDP speakers that can participate in MSDP mesh groups.

msdpMIBPeerGroup2.name: msdpMIBPeerGroup2
msdpMIBPeerGroup2.description: A collection of objects for managing MSDP peers.
